theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_interior_of_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A →
      closure (A : Set X) =
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  intro hP2
  -- First inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A)))`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) :=
    Topology.P2_implies_closure_subset_closure_interior_closure_interior
      (X := X) (A := A) hP2
  -- Second inclusion: `closure (interior (closure (interior A))) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (closure (interior A))) ⊆
        closure (A : Set X) := by
    -- Step 1: `interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure A`.
    have hIntSub :
        (interior (closure (interior A)) : Set X) ⊆
          closure (A : Set X) := by
      -- `interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
      have h₃ :
          (interior (closure (interior A)) : Set X) ⊆
            closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
        interior_subset
      -- `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`.
      have h₄ :
          closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
        closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A)
      exact h₃.trans h₄
    -- Taking closures preserves the inclusion.
    exact closure_mono hIntSub
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₂ h₁
